  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: `1.6.6`\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nCreation of the IPC file in the specified folder\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThe IPC path built always includes a \"\\\\.\\pipe\\\" before the path passed as argument. It gives no error, but the file is not created anywhere.\r\nI tried with absolute or relative path, and also eliminating the --ipcpath argument. The path it tries to open is always wrong with the \\\\.\\pipe\\ string\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ngeth --ipcpath whatever\\geth.ipc --datadir somedatadir -dev console\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n![capture](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3370901/27512030-43504d26-5934-11e7-9dbe-b47d40a87e40.JPG)\r\n\r\n",
